      "note_no": "64",
      "note": "According to a hadith on the authority of A'ishah, recorded in the Musnad of Ibn Hanbal, the Prophet \"used to divide his attentions equitably among his wives, and then would pray: 'O God! I am doing whatever is in my power: do not, then, blame me for [failing in] something which is in Thy power [alone], and not in mine!' thus alluding to his heart, and to loving some [of his wives] more than others.\""
